The paper proposes a semi-supervised active learning algorithm that uses a variational autoencoder (VAE) and an adversarial network to learn a latent space and a sampling mechanism for acquiring labeled data. This involves techniques from machine learning (VAE, adversarial training), computer vision (image classification, semantic segmentation), and natural language processing (text classification). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
